content.detailedDescription:
Halloween, 1952 - when i was very young, my father used to take me trick-or-treating around our neighborhood. in those days, commercial costumes were not available; so my mom made mine on her sewing machine from a pattern purchased locally: a bunny rabbit with long drooping ears. all of the houses in our neighborhood averaged about 100' from the street, and all had a walkway from the sidewalk to their stoop or front porch. i would walk up to the front door 
while my dad waited for me on the sidewalk parallel to the street. imagine my fear at six years old when i turned around to walk back down to the street,
and my father wasn't there. initially, panic overtook me until i spotted my dad in the middle of the street about one house down from the house where i had collected my candy. running towards him, i noticed he was looking up at the sky. i looked, too; and saw a perfect circle of rotating colored lights moving south to north. based on my memory, this ufo was about 500' in altitude and moving about 125-150 mph. the only other person we related this event to was my mother; and oddly enough, we never again talked about it amongst ourselves.
